    <title>'Font Name'  box doesn't update when the font is changed.</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Ubuntu Chromium/49.0.2623.108 Chrome/49.0.2623.108 Safari/537.36
Build Identifier: LibreOffice 5.1.2.2</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">When the Font Name menu is used, the box itself doesn't change the name it shows, it writes the new text over the last one, instead.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">This happens in every LibreOffice app and in every similar menu: Font Size, Paragraph Style, etc.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Changing the OpenCL options doesn't fix the problem, but it can be temporarely fixed if the LibreOffice window is minimized and then maximized.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">1 Open the 'Font Name' menu.</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.3">2 Change the font.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">The new font name is written on top of the old one.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="8">
            <sentence id="8.1">Expected Results:  
Only the new font name is shown inside the box.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
